reviews.text: My beautiful old home. My father , John Baxter, was the last light keeper in the early 70's. Many great old memories there from the hurricane to the copter landing on the road. Hoping to go back after all these years. If you live close or want to have a great vacation, visit Jamestown, it's a cute town and beautiful people that live there.

Another stunning location on Rhode Island's southern coast. Located in Beavertail State park. Great location for picnicking, sun bathing, kite flying, cast fishing, photography, hiking, jogging, sightseeing, and surf watch. Beware of ticks, and drop offs on the rocks. Be aware the rocks are slippery. Hold onto your kids and over confident teens.
Awesome place to go. Was very impressed. Wud definitely recommend going there 👍

Top five places to visit in Rhode Island. Phenomenal views all around of the water and the bay. Plenty of room to go for a walk. The rock formations around here just amazing. Perfect for picnics. Clean bathrooms.
One of my favorite places on the planet, my whole family loves it here, across three generations. Definitely a Must See! The museum is informative and interactive. ❤️🧡💛💚💙💜

So we wanted to see some cows, and we drove our little wimpy Versa all the way down their drive before realizing we were barking up the wrong tree. So we're trying to back down the drive (which is a pretty long, muddy beast), and wham we slide on down into a little ditch on the side of the road. Total miscalculation on our part. We're stuck in this mud, having planted our front wheel right in a spring, and it's not looking good. We're expecting whoever lives on this property to be irate at our intrusion but no-- these lovely people all came out, dogs and cats in tow, and helped us out of our pickle with some boards and a good push. They were lovely about the whole thing, and we've never been more grateful. 10/10 humans, lovely farm, and I'm sure the cows are great too. Hopefully we'll be back some day to see them.

A very welcome break from touring the mansions and historic homes and museums in the Providence Jamestown Newport area. My husband and I greatly enjoyed the walk, but some of the letters seem to be missing from the gates, so we did a bit of backtracking. None the less it was a delightful place to spend time. The vistas are marvelous, so any photographer will love it here period and small children could be run ragged!

Beautiful historic farm with really nice dogs. You can walk down various paths to get to the beach, but it's a long and hot walk (not many trees) if you're with kids. It's a great place to spend an afternoon! Just make sure you go on their website before you plan on going, because there are only certain days where you can actually go there.
Really awesome walking trails. It reminds me of the English or Irish country side.
Good walk through the fields down to the bay.
Beautiful area!  The building is historical and small, but full of interesting photos and information. If you like history and relaxing vacations, this is a good place to visit

Learning about where you are is always a great idea and this charming historical society is absorbing, friendly, and a great way to spend an hour or so browsing the finer details of American history that few explore.
Love our history...

great place to visit in Jamestown, RI
Museum open in Summer 1 - 4 pm Wed. thru Sun.

Fantastic little spot that's been a consistent local favorite. The menu is pretty big but every option is delicious. Slightly on the pricier side but I'd say it's worth it. The gorgeous view out onto the water is an added bonus!

Their sandwiches are delicious, I've tried a few different ones... the liverwurst with red onion was excellent... a generous cut of liverwurst and the roll was fresh... there's not another place in Rhode Island that has liverwurst offered in a sandwich...I'm hooked !!!  The young staff works hard and don't say much as they go through their tasks.
Service is great and friendly. Coffee and hit chocolate are always hot and tasty. And the food is great
This little place has a lot of wonderful sandwiches, right with a view of the bay! I was surprised at how much this little place has to offer.
simple supplies here. nothing wrong but nothing special either
Good food. Big portions. A couple could share the peppered chicken which is great.  Expect to spend about $10 to $15 a person if not sharing. Nice employees.

The owner is a wonderful woman and the food is to die for. It's beyond Chinese takeout, this place is a legit fine dining Mandarin restaurant. Their red pepper chicken is my favorite Chinese dish ever!

One of my favorite restaurants in Champaign-Urbana. My family goes all the time, the owner knows us and starts our regular dishes as soon as we walk in. Spicy diced chicken, spicy fish in broth, stuffed tofu, and seafood in XO sauce. They have HUGE tables and a room in the back, great for big parties and the workers are always super nice. Highly recommend :)

Got food because we wanted Chinese and the place was close. Was pleasantly surprised that the food came quickly and tasted great! The lunch deal was a steal as well! Would recommend for anyone wanting to grab some Chinese!
I absolutely love coming to this place!  The food is awesome and the staff is wonderful!!  I come in at least once a week.

This is a good spot for a quick bite to eat or a scoop of ice cream if you happen to be in Jamestown. The menu consists of mostly wraps, burgers and sandwich options. They have outdoor seating by the dock which, if you can grab an open table, is always the best way to go. They also serve beer and wine which I think is a new addition to the menu.

Ice cream is average however is extremely overpriced!!! Asked for mac n Cheese it was 4$ and guess what.. it was just kraft mac n cheese, nothing wrong with kraft was just hoping for some quality food

Ordered whole belly clam plate..they told me and everybody else that it would be 45 minutes...came back 35 minutes later. They said plate was cold because it was ready a while ago..they did offer me fresh French  fries...the food was horrible..I would have gotten better food if I went to frozen section of any supermarket..which I suspect is where they get their food....I will say that the people who work there are very friendly..will not go back
Seaside was awesome. American food was available during summer time
Great little nook on the water. Good local beers. Food and dessert were delicious. Friendly staff as well.

Doesn't even deserve a star. Worst most bland food ever. Looked great and smelled great. And then you take a bite. Just no. I got the maple mustard salmon with coleslaw and fries. Salmon was burnt and was hard. The sauce was too acidic. Fries had no flavor needed lots of salt. The coleslaw was super old and was so gross. The waitress was just bland as well. The only thing they have going for them is the interior decor.

absolutely the best seafood in RI,  FRESH AND PERFECTLY COOKED! I recommend the seafood au gratin! exquisite. ..the waitress awesome and the chef Dave... one of a kind...so good we had to sing to him after our meal! ....The New England Gospel Ensemble.
Great bar, good food and service!
Good local fair

A neighborhood gem with fresh seafood, specials that include 2 entrees and a bottle of wine, staff that seem to love their job and more.   On street parking with often a walk to get to the location.   Not particularly accessible to those with ambulatory difficulties, especially those needing full sized wheel chairs.  Narrow aisles and doorways.  Atmosphere of antique nautical.

This is a nice cozy place with excellent coastal views. The rooms were accommodating enough for 2 people. The front desk, restaurant and maintenance staff were very pleasant. I would recommend staying here.
Staff is very friendly, ("Cat" did an amazing job). Food is nice.  The view is exceptional.

Get little getaway,  and stay over in this beautiful place,  enjoying waterfront from your windows,  beautiful views, and awesome atmosphere inside! Place is clean, warm and cozy! Would like to come back again!

Nice hotel, great location but the doors were sticky, and one of my closet doors was off the hinge. Couldn't close the curtains all the way, and there was old popcorn stuck in my couch cushions. Lovely inn but a little lacking on the details.
Friendly, being remodeled, our room looking out on the bay is great.

Always a pleasure to eat here. Such a lovely setting whether you eat upstairs or downstairs. We enjoy a casual after work dinner at the upstairs bar. Food is consistently good. Bartenders are attentive and make great cocktails.

The space, food, service and ambience are well worth taking a trip to dine at this lovely updated Jamestown restaurant!! The salad was fresh and inventive. The rolls were warm and tasty. The pasta entrees were delicious! The menu has something for everyone whether you want a light appetizer such as tuna or a burger or a full entree. There are specially created cocktails and a great selection of wines and beers. The space is simply gorgeous. You can dine at one of the bars or patios on the first or second levels or choose a variety of al fresco locations. The decor is country chic meets beach house. You will want to ask the owners where they found all the different things and if they can build and decorate your next house!!
Delicious, friendly staff and reasonably priced food.

It's very expensive and there's nothing that really stands out about the cuisine. The location was amazing the staff was really great too. Service was top notch but the food was just very mediocre and considerably over priced in my opinion. Also, 10$ per bottled beer is greedy.

Wonderful setting and location, but...
We had a reunion of friends last year who had been frequent diners and drinkers at this restaurant and recently tried it again to see if things had improved. NO. The food was pedestrian, (mediocre), the mussels were served with many not opened, and the prices were exceptionally high for not exceptional food.Be prepared for high priced drinks as well. Good service, but had hoped it would have been a better experience.
